      "content": "I understand your frustration and desire to avoid unnecessary expenses and side effects. However, stopping antibiotics prematurely can lead to incomplete treatment, which can cause the infection to return and potentially become resistant to the medication. This can make it harder to treat in the future and may result in more severe health consequences. While it's tempting to assume the bacteria are dead with no redness, the infection may still be present at a level not yet detectable. Your health and the effectiveness of antibiotics are at stake here. It is always best to consult with a healthcare professional before making changes to your medication regimen.",
